
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-iab-link-indications-10.txt'>
    <title>"Architectural Implications of Link Indications", Bernard Aboba</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-iab-link-indications-10.txt</link>
    <description>A link indication represents information provided by the link layer to higher layers regarding the state of the link. This document describes the role of link indications within the Internet Architecture. While the judicious use of link indications can provide performance benefits, inappropriate use can degrade both robustness and performance. This document summarizes current proposals, describes the architectural issues and provides examples of appropriate and inappropriate uses of link indications.</description>
    <dc:date>2007-03-01T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
